pullRequest.body:
We introduce the `omega'` function enumerating the initial ordinals, as well as the more standard `omega` skipping over finite ordinals.

---

I'm all for good documentation, but I don't think it makes sense to tag lemmas about `omega'` or `aleph'` when the functions themselves already have good documentation differentiating them from their unprimed variants, so I just disabled the linter for these sections of the file.
